# Data Fetching & Mutations

## Query & Mutation Helpers — `src/db/queries/`

All database interactions must be extracted into dedicated helper functions living in `src/db/queries/`. Never write Drizzle queries inline inside Server Components or Server Actions — always call a helper from this directory instead.

Organize files by domain (e.g. `src/db/queries/decks.ts`, `src/db/queries/cards.ts`). Each file exports typed async functions that encapsulate the query or mutation logic.

```ts
// src/db/queries/decks.ts
import { db } from "@/db";
import { decksTable } from "@/db/schema";
import { eq, and } from "drizzle-orm";

export async function getDecksByUser(userId: string) {
  return db.select().from(decksTable).where(eq(decksTable.userId, userId));
}

export async function getDeckWithCards(deckId: string, userId: string) {
  return db.query.decksTable.findFirst({
    where: and(eq(decksTable.id, deckId), eq(decksTable.userId, userId)),
    with: { cards: true },
  });
}

export async function createDeck(userId: string, name: string, description?: string) {
  const [deck] = await db
    .insert(decksTable)
    .values({ userId, name, description })
    .returning();
  return deck;
}
```

## Data Retrieval — Server Components Only

Always fetch data in React Server Components by calling a helper from `src/db/queries/`. Never fetch data on the client side (no `useEffect` + `fetch`, no SWR/React Query calling API routes for initial data).

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — Server Component calling a query helper
import { getDecksByUser } from "@/db/queries/decks";

export default async function DecksPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  const decks = await getDecksByUser(userId);
  return <DeckList decks={decks} />;
}

// ❌ BAD — inline Drizzle query in a Server Component
const decks = await db.select().from(decksTable).where(eq(decksTable.userId, userId));

// ❌ BAD — Client-side fetching
"use client";
useEffect(() => { fetch("/api/decks").then(...) }, []);
```

## Mutations — Server Actions Only

All inserts, updates, and deletes must be implemented as Next.js Server Actions that delegate to a helper in `src/db/queries/`. Never use API routes (`/app/api/`) for mutations, and never write Drizzle mutation logic directly inside a Server Action.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — Server Action calling a mutation helper
"use server";
import { createDeck } from "@/db/queries/decks";

export async function createDeckAction(data: CreateDeckInput) {
  const parsed = createDeckSchema.safeParse(data);
  if (!parsed.success) throw new Error("Invalid input");
  return createDeck(userId, parsed.data.name, parsed.data.description);
}

// ❌ BAD — inline Drizzle insert inside a Server Action
await db.insert(decksTable).values({ userId, name, description });

// ❌ BAD — API route mutation
// POST /api/decks/route.ts
```

## Validation — Zod Required

All data passed to server actions must be:
1. Validated with a Zod schema
2. Typed with a TypeScript type derived from that schema (use `z.infer<>`)
3. Never typed as `FormData`

```ts
import { z } from "zod";

const createDeckSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1).max(100),
  description: z.string().max(500).optional(),
});

type CreateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof createDeckSchema>;

export async function createDeckAction(data: CreateDeckInput) {
  const parsed = createDeckSchema.safeParse(data);
  if (!parsed.success) throw new Error("Invalid input");
  // delegate to query helper — no raw Drizzle here
  return createDeck(userId, parsed.data.name, parsed.data.description);
}
```
